        "paragraph_zA7NDM": {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "green_label": "",
            "white_label": "",
            "title": "From Historical Evolution to Technological Innovation",
            "h2_text": false,
            "content": "<p>In the past, sailors relied on heavy, impractical garments often made of wool, a material that provided decent wind and water protection but was neither comfortable nor flexible. Over time, lighter and more protective technical fabrics were introduced, radically transforming sailing garments.<\/p>",
            "button_text": "",
            "button_url": "",
            "is_new_tab": false,
            "variant_color": "green",
            "truncate_text": false
          }
        },
        "paragraph_Jj6AwV": {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "green_label": "",
            "white_label": "",
            "title": "The Turning Point: An Innovative Approach to Technology and Material Selection",
            "h2_text": false,
            "content": "<p>The real breakthrough in this sector came with the introduction of garments that not only provided effective protection but also ensured comfort and performance. The key aspects of this turning point are:<\/p><ul><li><strong>Use of Waterproof and Breathable Technical Fabrics<\/strong>: To keep sailors dry while allowing good ventilation, protecting them from the elements, including the sun.<br\/><\/li><li><strong>Importance of Functional Design<\/strong>: To maximize fluidity and speed of movement on board, which can make the difference in a regatta.<br\/><\/li><li><strong>Continuous Dialogue with Athletes<\/strong>: To test and implement garments in the most extreme conditions of use.<\/li><\/ul>",
            "button_text": "",
            "button_url": "",
            "is_new_tab": false,
            "variant_color": "green",
            "truncate_text": false
          }
        }
      },
