        "title": "MickeyBear Fleece: The First Fleece Garment Designed for Sailors",
        "content": "<p>One of the first significant innovations in technical sailing garments developed by our company is the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.slam.com\/it\/blogs\/slam-stories\/mickey-bear-il-maglione-che-ha-segnato-un-epoca\">Mickey<br\/>Bear Fleece<\/a>, , which debuted in 1979 when SLAM was still in its infancy (Why is it called that? That's another story). <br\/>The use of \"fleece\" instead of wool ensured more warmth and better moisture management: \"The Mickey Bear Fleece was a game-changer. It kept us warm and dry in the toughest conditions, allowing us to focus on our performance,\" said Dodo Gorla, bronze medalist at the 1980 Moscow Olympics alongside Alfio Pieraboni.<\/p>",
        "variant_color": "green"
