            "title": "Design for Performance: Sailing Jacket, the First Short Sailing Jacket",
            "h2_text": false,
            "content": "<p>In the early '90s, we introduced the Sailing Jacket, the first short sailing jacket on the market.<br\/>Until then, most oilskins were knee-length, making movements on the boat less agile and fluid. <br\/>The practical, simple, and comfortable design of the Sailing Jacket made it an immediate success. <br\/>This historic jacket is still in production today in its winter version, the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.slam.com\/products\/man-sailing-warm-jacket-a123007s00?_pos=7&_sid=5314a7609&_ss=r\">Sailing Warm Jacket,<\/a> and summer version, the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.slam.com\/products\/man-sailing-jacket-a123008s00?_pos=1&_sid=5314a7609&_ss=r\">Sailing Jacket<\/a>. Optimized in terms of materials and design, they continue to accompany sailors and sports enthusiasts faithfully.<\/p>",
            "button_text": "",
            "button_url": "",
            "is_new_tab": false,
            "variant_color": "green",
